			<div class="content" id="post-content-358575">
									

<p>I like this one, just a question though. It was a computer refined on 1:1 right? with 808 present, meaning it's a equal but different mechanical/clockwork version… so where is the extra-dimensional space coming from? clockwork can't create extra-dimensional space. extra-dimensional isn't equal to any part in a computer. it sounds too advanced. something powered by a void and noneuclidean geometry doesn't seem the same as getting powered by electricity. now i understand why you did it, logistic problems, but maybe instead of trying to find a loophole so the computer can fit in a room yet be explored, just roll with the problems. make the problem of giant computer suddenly appearing part of the story.</p>
<p>oh! <em>dammit i hate it when I'm inspired in other peoples posts! i have an idea yet can't do anything about it! :)</em> How about they put the computer in and then, bam, the room starts shaking, and this huge computer, size of a football stadium, bursts threw the roof, covering the entire area. and the main conflict is, the gear machine, one of our most valuable SCPS, is stuck inside this thing, right in the center. and so now, these people (from anther base, since the base where the computer is is stuck inside the computer…maybe even the computer is incorporating the SCPs and foundation technology inside itself making them processors or something. maybe even using the refiner's power? although that might ruin the idea) have to journey inside this mad place, past moving gears, to try to find it again, rescue the doctors, and 808 as well. In the end they could shrink it and create extra-dimensional space with another SPC somehow, so there could still be fun experiments on it. This all could be the prequel or background information. Or they could just shrink or destroy it with out extra-dimensional space, and your current journal entires would be part of the search for 808, the refiner machine, and the doctors arc.</p>

