<p>808's aura would probably want it to be pushed towards increased reliance on electron quantum states, since she's a conduit for, as Fish puts it, a "universe of pure electronic order".</p>
<p>914, however, wasn't having any of that. I'm still divided as to whether 914 was afraid of 808 the conduit, or trying to help out 808 the person. Or maybe 914 just got bored and decided introducing extradimensional space would be a nifty thing to try.</p>
<p>And technically, the space in 915 is the same space in the input computer. It's just been… stretched, folded, and knotted a little.</p>
<p><em>edit:</em> And I guess I should clarify by saying I anthropomorphize 914, but that's a personal interpretation. I see 914 developing intelligence as a Boltzmann brain — entirely randomly and accidental.</p>

