<p>oh thats interesting. what I assumed was since 808 wanted something mechanical around her, so she could actually use it(because theres a ban on anything else in her quarters), 808 just followed her command. or that 914 interpeted that a mechanical object would be more useful to her because it wouldn't get taken away. but now that i think about it, that no longer seems right.</p>
<p>instead, that 914 turns any object around 808 into something she can't control to combat her/balance the conflicting powers out is my new pet theory. maybe if the Robot Apocalypse ever comes, it can be foreshadowed by objects being refined into purely mechanical tools, with no reliance on electronics. because whats more useful, a tool that can be controlled by the Machine God, or one that is completely resistant to her. near the end, what researchers ask for a more useful tool, strangely they get something that seems almost primitive… (guy puts into a gun with targeting sights and laser beams, gets back a club "A club, how is that more useful then a gun?" …oh you'll see…) That could become 914 sole function, just to hint at what's going to happen very soon… You know, i might write a foundation tale about that… The idea that these guys are putting in computers, and getting mechanical ones, that capitalize on 808s weakness, is just really cool. like 914 met 808 for the first time, and figured her out… and now it's preparing us…</p>

